h3#description Description
p
	| Here's a list of CSS Library that are part of Chico Mobile look and feel. They will help you with common layout elements, such as buttons and tables.
a.more(href="/static/demos/mobile.html", target="_blank") See a complete demo

h3#headers Headers
.ch-g1-2
	.ch-leftcolumn
		h4 Demo
		iframe.mobile-demo(src="/mobile/demos/headers", style="height:125px")
		p
			a.more(href="/static/demos/mobile.html", target="_blank") See a complete demo
		p
			a.more(href="/mobile/guides/change-the-header-color") See how to change the Header color
.ch-g1-2
	.ch-rightcolumn
		h4 Markup
		p
			| By using the classname 
			code ch-header
			|  or 
			code ch-header-skin
			|  you'll get a simple bar where you can add your custom elements.
		p
			| There's some presetted elements that you can use in your header, such as an 
			code &lt;h1&gt;
			|  tag (this will be appear centered) and a 
			code &lt;nav&gt;
			|  tag, where you can add buttons with class 
			code ch-btn-header
			|  and locate it at left (
			code ch-action-left
			| ) or right (
			code ch-action-right
			| ).
		p
			| For example:
		pre
			| <header class="ch-header">
			| 	<h1>Main header</h1>
			| 	<nav>
			| 		<a class="ch-btn-header ch-action-left" href="#">Cancel</a>
			| 		<a class="ch-btn-header ch-action-right" href="#">Accept</a>
			| 	</nav>
			| </header>
		p
			| Also, you can 
			a(href="/mobile/guides/change-the-header-color") change the Header color
			| .
.clearfix

h3#buttons Buttons
.ch-g1-2
	.ch-leftcolumn
		h4 Demo
		iframe.mobile-demo(src="/mobile/demos/buttons", style="height:660px")
		a.more(href="/static/demos/mobile.html", target="_blank") See a complete demo
.ch-g1-2
	.ch-rightcolumn
		h4 Markup
		p
			| You can transform these elements into a styled button:
		ul.ch-list
			li
				code &lt;a&gt;
			li
				code &lt;button&gt;
			li
				code &lt;input type="submit" />
			li
				code &lt;input type="button" />
		p
			| You just need to add the classname 
			code ch-btn
			| :
		pre <input type="submit" value="Send" class="ch-btn" />
		p
			| To change the button size, you have to add as second classname one of these:
		ul.ch-list
			li
				code ch-btn-big
			li
				code ch-btn-small
		p
			| To change the button skin, you have to change the first classname to one of these:
		ul.ch-list
			li
				code ch-btn-skin
			li
				code ch-btn-action
		p
			| To disable it, add the 
			code ch-btn-disabled
			|  classname.
		p
			strong You can add an icon within a button!
			|  We have a 
			a(href="/mobile/guides/add-an-icon-within-a-button") complete guide
			|  you must see.
.clearfix

